## Step 6: Perform the actual calculation
The ionization energy of $\mathrm{H}_2 = D_0(\mathrm{H}_2) + IP(\mathrm{H}) - D_0(\mathrm{H}_2^{+}) = 4.478 \mathrm{eV} + 13.598 \mathrm{eV} - 2.651 \mathrm{eV}$.

